'''Lisa Small''' is an American art historian and museum curator. She is a curator of Exhibitions at the [[Brooklyn Museum]], and most widely known for her 2014 blockbuster exhibition, [[Killer Heels]].<ref name=Ziamou>{{cite news|last1=Ziamou|first1=Lalia|title=Lisa Small: On Curating "Killer Heels: The Art of the High-Heeled Shoe"|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/lilia-ziamou/lisa-small-on-curating-ki_b_6678988.html|accessdate=13 August 2015|publisher=Huffington Post|date=16 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=Wray>{{cite news|last1=Wray|first1=Adam|title=Soles on Display at the Brooklyn Museum|url=http://redef.com/original/soles-on-display-at-the-brooklyn-museum|accessdate=13 August 2015|publisher=Redef|date=30 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=Smith>{{cite news|last1=Smith|first1=Roberta|title=Fantasies From Pandora‚Äôs Shoe Box|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/12/arts/design/a-feast-of-killer-shoes-at-the-brooklyn-museum.html|accessdate=13 August 2015|publisher=New York Times|date=11 September 2014}}</ref><ref name="CrymHeels">{{cite news|last1=Crum|first1=Maddie|title=Why Are Powerful Women Icons Always Wearing High Heels?|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/why-are-powerful-women-icons-always-wearing-high-heels_us_57155a91e4b0060ccda41a5d|accessdate=1 May 2016|publisher=HuffPost|date=27 April 2016}}</ref>

