'''''The New Book of Knowledge''''' is an [[encyclopedia]] intended primarily for children from 3rd to 8th grades.<ref name="Official">{{cite web|url=http://www.scholastic.ca/education/library/encyclopedias/nbk.html|title=Official site for 2008 edition|work=Scholastic Press|accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref>

It was based on [[Grolier]]'s older ''[[The Children's Encyclop√¶dia|Book of Knowledge]]''.<ref>Funk & Wagnalls New Encyclopedia, 1996</ref>
The ''New Book of Knowledge'' was originally published by Grolier in the 1940s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://openlibrary.org/b/OL5988842M|title=The Open Library - The New Book of Knowledge [1st ed. &#0093;|accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> Currently published by [[Scholastic Corporation|Scholastic Press]], it has gone through several editions. The 2007 edition is published in 21 volumes and contains more than 9,000 articles.<ref name="Official"/> By an agreement with Scholastic, Grolier published the contents of the encyclopedia online with registration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infohio.org/Er/Preview2007/grolier2007.html|title=Grolier Online Preview 2007|work=Infohio|accessdate=2007-12-11}}</ref> In 2000, Scholastic Corporation acquired Grolier and now has full rights to the contents of ''The New Book of Knowledge''.
